dataIdInfo.idAbs: This point data layer represents addresses for Sheboygan County, Wisconsin at year-end 2016. It is a feature dataset within the geodatabase 'Sheboygan_Addresses_YE2016'. [Site address points represent the location of site or service delivery addresses assigned by local governments. Sheboygan County Planning & Conservation Department assigns and enters all addresses outside of Cities & Villages.All City & Village addresses are entered when the Planning Department is informed of them.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Site Address Points for Sheboygan County WI]

Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements.
This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.
